    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Cresson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Threatened cabinet crisis following diplomatic council and censure of Peruvian
                    minister for foreign affairs’ policy by Pardo and his group has been averted.
                    Peruvian minister for foreign affairs will not resign. He informed me this
                    afternoon Ecuadorians are ready to negotiate amicable settlement for recent
                    rioting. He seems to be more in the hope of amicable settlement whole
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cresson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
